#Summary1=(human1) This article details some of the history of Cleveland, Ohio, and its attractions, including museums (the Cleveland Museum of Art, HealthSpace, Rock and Roll Hall of Fame), professional sports venues (Progressive Field, QuickenLoans Arena, Cleveland Browns Stadium, Wolstein Center), most golf courses per capita in the US, and a "Big Five" orchestra.

#Summary2=(claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022) Cleveland, a culturally rich metropolitan area on Lake Erie's shore, evolved from a major industrial center into a diverse urban hub featuring world-class museums, sports venues, performing arts centers, and recreational facilities, while serving as a model for effective urban revitalization.

#Summary3=(gpt4o) Cleveland, the “Comeback City” on Lake Erie, has evolved from a manufacturing hub to a center for healthcare, law, and finance, featuring cultural attractions like the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame, Cleveland Orchestra, and Playhouse Square, making it a lively destination for international visitors.

#Summary4=(Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct) Cleveland is a culturally diverse and economically revitalized city in Northeast Ohio, USA, known for its rich cultural resources, recreational opportunities, and iconic attractions, such as the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame and Museum, and its efforts to become a model of sustainable urban planning.

#Summary5=(Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct) Cleveland, a culturally diverse city on the shores of Lake Erie in Ohio, has undergone significant revitalization and is now recognized as a model of effective public-private partnerships for urban planning, boasting numerous cultural attractions, sports facilities, and economic diversity despite its historical ties to industry.
#Text=Cleveland is a culturally diverse city on the shores of Lake Erie , one of the Great Lakes , in Cuyahoga County , Ohio , USA .
#Text=Recreational , cultural and educational opportunities are abundant throughout Northeast Ohio .
#Text=You 'll find world - class museums and cultural events , professional sports and amusement parks , and the most golf courses per capita in the United States .
#Text=Places Rated Almanac ranks the area second in recreational options out of 354 US metro areas .
#Text=Plus , this region ranks fifth in the nation in number of major cultural resources per one million residents .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Cleveland from lakefront .
#Text=Cleveland is the urban center of Northeast Ohio , the 15th largest combined metropolitan area in the United States .
#Text=Throughout the twentieth century , the City of Cleveland proper was ranked as one of the 10 largest cities in the U.S. ( from 1890 until 1970 per US Census Bureau statistics ) .
#Text=Like most U.S. cities , Cleveland proper began to lose population to suburban areas in the 1960s and 1970s .
#Text=However , in the mid-1980s , Cleveland earned the nickname the " Comeback City " as the urban core experienced a dramatic revitalization process that continues today .

column1: #Text=As its " comeback " has continued , the official moniker is now the New American City as Cleveland has rightfully earned the reputation as a model of effective public - private partnership for urban planning .

#Text=Despite the common perception that Cleveland is an industrial town , just beyond the automotive and steel plants , a clean and beautiful downtown rises at the mouth of the Cuyahoga River on the southern shore of Lake Erie ( often marvelled over by visitors who are surprised you ca n't see the other side , i.e. , Canada ) .
#Text=Like other cities in the so - called " rust belt “ , Cleveland has endured growing pains as it makes its transition from a manufacturing - based economy .

#Text=Another thing non-locals do n't often realize is that Cleveland 's long history of industrial wealth has left it chock full of cultural riches as well as the beginnings of a  sustainable city " movement .

column1: #Text=Serving as a global model for urban rebirth , Cleveland has been named one of the top 10 international visitor hotspots by Travel and Leisure magazine .

#Text=For decades , the city has boasted of : a " Big Five " orchestra ( The Cleveland Orchestra ) , the second largest performing arts center in the U.S. ( Playhouse Square Center ) , a world - renowned art museum ( The Cleveland Museum of Art ) , the nation 's first health museum ( HealthSpace Cleveland ) , R&D hub of the aerospace and aviation industry ( the NASA Glenn Research & Visitors Center ) and a number of other first - rate attractions ( too many to mention here - read on ) .

column1: #Text=During its " comeback " years , Cleveland has added : the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame and Museum , the Great Lakes Science Center with Omnimax theatre , and four new sports facilities in the downtown area - Progressive Field ( Still known as " The Jake " after a recent corporate name change ) for the Major League Baseball Indians , QuickenLoans Arena ( " The Q " ) for the NBA Cavaliers , Cleveland Browns Stadium for the NFL Browns and the Wolstein Center for the Cleveland State University Vikings basketball team .
